occurrenceRemarks: A rare species of Heuchera, grotto alumroot is a plant of extremes. It is almost always found growing under rock overhangs, in cracks. Sites are usually in full shade in virtually no soil, and no water, relying mostly on whatever moisture condenses or runs through the fractures in the rock. Found in only a few locations in Hickory Nut Gorge. Blooms from late July into September.
More of this stuff that likes to grow on rock ledges. Angel Windows trail.
